# Zenmart â€“ Quick Commerce Platform

A full-stack Quick Commerce (Q-Commerce) web application inspired by Zepto. This platform includes customer ordering, warehouse management, delivery estimation, and product inventory management.

---

# 1. Customer Application Features

## 1.1 Global Search
- Search products globally across all categories
- Show:
  - Popular searches
  - Suggested products
  - Category-based results

---

## 1.2 Profile Settings

User profile includes:

- View order history
- Manage addresses
- Edit profile details
- Logout functionality

---

## 1.3 Cart Functionality

### Cart Persistence
- Cart should remain saved even after browser refresh or reopening

### Cart Components

Cart design includes:

- Address selection and change option
- Coupons application
- Cart items list
- Bill summary:
  - Item total
  - Delivery charge
  - Discount
  - Final amount (To Pay)
- Delivery instructions input
- Delivery partner tip option
- Suggested products ("You might also like")
- Receiver details:
  - Receiver name (editable)
  - Phone number (editable)

---

## 1.4 Payment Options

Support multiple payment methods:

- UPI
- Credit/Debit Card
- Net Banking
- Cash on Delivery
- Wallets

---

## 1.5 Location and Delivery Time Calculation

Features:

- Change delivery location
- Delivery time calculated based on:


Factors:

- Nearest warehouse selection
- Distance between warehouse and delivery location
- Real-time availability

---

# 2. APIs Required

## 2.1 Product APIs

### Get all products
- List all products

### Get products by category

Categories include:

- All
- Cafe
- Home
- Toys
- Fresh
- Household
- Rice
- Skincare

---

### Buy Again API

- Show previously purchased products

---

### Specialized Category API

- Household items
- Skincare
- Grocery
- Personal care

---

## 2.2 Banner APIs

Banner types:

- Discount banners
- Special offer banners
- Special news banners
- Festival / Special day banners

---

## 2.3 Website Metadata APIs

Includes:

- General website information
- Popular searches
- Categories list
- Footer details
- Footer banner content

---

# 3. Warehouse Management System (Dark Store)

Warehouse system used by warehouse owners and partners.

---

## 3.1 Warehouse Authentication

Warehouse owner login:

- Email / Username
- Password authentication

Warehouse partners include:

- Supermarkets
- Wholesale markets
- Dark stores
- Example: Dmart partner warehouse

---

## 3.2 Nearby Warehouse Settings

Features:

- Detect nearest warehouse
- Assign warehouse based on delivery location
- Warehouse distance calculation

---

## 3.3 Warehouse Master Module

Warehouse details include:

- Warehouse ID
- Warehouse Name
- Location
- Partner Name
- Created Date
- Updated Date

---

# 4. Product Management (Warehouse Side)

Warehouse can manage products using:

## 4.1 Manual Product Creation

Fields:

- Brand name
- Product name
- Product category
- Price
- Product image
- Quantity
- Warehouse location
- Created date
- Updated date
- Stock quantity

---

## 4.2 Bulk Upload

- Upload products via file (CSV / Excel)

---

## 4.3 Scan Upload

- Add product using barcode / QR scan

---

## 4.4 Stock Management

Features:

- Update stock quantity
- View stock list
- Track stock availability
- Low stock alert

---

# 5. Core System Modules Overview

| Module | Description |
|------|-------------|
| Customer App | Browse products, cart, order, payment |
| Profile System | User profile, orders, address management |
| Cart System | Persistent cart with billing and suggestions |
| Payment System | Multiple payment integrations |
| Warehouse System | Product and inventory management |
| Product API | Product listing, categories, search |
| Banner System | Dynamic marketing banners |
| Location System | Warehouse selection and delivery calculation |

---

# 6. Future Enhancements

Possible improvements:

- Real-time delivery tracking
- Delivery partner app
- Admin dashboard
- Analytics dashboard
- AI product recommendations
- Push notifications

---

# 7. Technology Stack (Recommended)

## Frontend
- React.js
- Next.js
- Tailwind CSS

## Backend
- Node.js
- Express.js

## Database
- MongoDB

## Storage
- AWS S3 / Cloudinary (images)

## Authentication
- JWT

